          "milestone": {},
          "comments": 13,
          "created_at": "2025-02-26T01:05:34Z",
          "updated_at": "2025-12-26T09:56:10Z",
          "closed_at": "2025-02-26T18:41:27Z",
          "author_association": "MEMBER",
          "type": {},
          "active_lock_reason": {},
          "draft": false,
          "pull_request": {
            "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/python/cpython/pulls/130562",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/130562",
            "diff_url": "https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/130562.diff",
            "patch_url": "https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/130562.patch",
            "merged_at": "2025-02-26T18:41:27Z"
          },
          "body": "The WITH_EXCEPT_START opcode is getting the traceback from the exception object and then passing it down via a vectorcall, but only after decref'ing the traceback. \r\n\r\nBut the exception object can have the only reference to the traceback. If the receiver of the traceback does something to cause the exception's trace back to be replaced, then uses the traceback, they access dangling pointer. The traceback shouldn't solely be kept alive by the exception object which can be mutated.\n\n<!-- gh-issue-number: gh-130595 -->\n* Issue: gh-130595\n<!-- /gh-issue-number -->\n",
          "closed_by": {
            "login": "DinoV",
            "id": 320265,
            "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMyMDI2NQ==",
            "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/320265?v=4",
